  "title": "R&D Operation Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Operate, monitor, and optimise <strong>advanced electrochemical systems and supporting process equipment</strong>\nat lab/pilot scale. Design small experiments, analyse data, and collaborate with partners (universities/commercial) to drive operational improvements.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Operate and document performance of systems and subsystems; assist maintenance & troubleshooting.</li><li>Design small‑scale experiments; analyse datasets; propose improvements to procedures and controls.</li><li>Conduct field‑based chemical/physical tests; ensure compliance with EHS protocols.</li><li>Manage sub‑projects for subsystems or technical challenges; coordinate with external partners.</li><li>Maintain accurate records of conditions, deviations, and results; write memos & reports.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Chemical/Mechanical/Electrical or related.</li><li>2–6+ years in pilot operations, reliability/maintenance, or test engineering.</li><li>Strong documentation, communication, and cross‑functional collaboration skills.</li></ul>",
